{
  "stem": "4289.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I ran away from there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I don't know what happened to that woman after that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know what resulted out of it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I believe that police stopped it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's my belief because that was it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And at the same time, when this rumor was going around, my aunt and uncle, who came from Siberia-- my aunt Roma and my uncle-- when they heard the news-- my uncle told me later-- Roma said, that sounds like our Ida.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were in Sosnowiec.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they came to Czestochowa to check me out when they heard that this is possible that it's Ida.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because I guess my aunt, before she died, she told anybody, and everybody in the family that one child maybe will survive this war.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And will be one of the twins.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they came, and they looked at me from far, and they told me later, that I did look like my sister at the same time because when they knew my sister, she was about seven, eight.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when they saw me after the war, I was about the same age.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they saw the resemblance.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At the same time, my own father came back from Russia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when he came, he went straight to Sosnowiec to see who is-- who else is there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he found out that he lost his wife and children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But there was still this rumor that one of the twins is still alive in Czestochowa.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when he met with Uncle Joe and Aunt Roma, they told him, you have to go to Czestochowa and check out this child.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was 1946.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he did come.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, Aunt Rozia had the same end, end as my mother.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was walked from Auschwitz to Germany, at the end of the war, almost.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
